10</ArticleId></ArticleIdList><ReferenceList><Reference><Citation>S. A. Goutman, O. Hardiman, A. Al&#x2010;Chalabi, et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Recent Advances in the Diagnosis and Prognosis of Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis,&#x201d; Lancet Neurology 21, no. 5 (2022): 480&#x2013;493.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>M. Garret, K. Mehta, J. Y. Chen, and S. Babu, &#x201c;Rise of the Genomic Medicine Era in Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis,&#x201d; Practical Neurology 22, no. 6 (2023): 22&#x2013;27.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>T. M. Miller, M. E. Cudkowicz, A. Genge, et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Trial of Antisense Oligonucleotide Tofersen for SOD1 ALS,&#x201d; New England Journal of Medicine 387, no. 12 (2022): 1099&#x2013;1110.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>J. L. Cerillo and P. M. Tofersen, StatPearls (Treasure Island (FL), 2025).</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>T. M. Miller, M. E. Cudkowicz, P. J. Shaw, et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Long&#x2010;Term Tofersen in SOD1 Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis,&#x201d; JAMA Neurology 83 (2025): e254946, https://doi.org/10.1001/jamaneurol.2025.4946.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>C. Quinn, E. A. Macklin, N. Atassi, et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Post&#x2010;Lumbar Puncture Headache Is Reduced With Use of Atraumatic Needles in ALS,&#x201d; Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis &amp; Frontotemporal Degeneration 14, no. 7&#x2013;8 (2013): 632&#x2013;634, https://doi.org/10.3109/21678421.2013.808227.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>M. Yerton, A. Winter, D. Gelevski, et&#xa0;al., &#x201c;Expanded Access Protocol (EAP) Program for Access to Investigational Products for Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS),&#x201d; Muscle &amp; Nerve 67, no. 6 (2023): 456&#x2013;463.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>M. Huang, Y. U. Liu, X. Yao, D. Qin, and H. Su, &#x201c;Variability in SOD1&#x2010;Associated Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis: Geographic Patterns, Clinical Heterogeneity, Molecular Alterations, and Therapeutic 